content:
Analyze Your Data

Salesforce Analytics Tools
Reports and Dashboards
Manage Your Reports and Dashboards on Analytics Home
Considerations When Using Reports in the Salesforce Mobile App
Number of Rows Displayed: 2,000 rows maximum
Groupings: displayed as columns at the end of the report
Report Formats: grouped by rows or matrix, without groupings; joined reports not available

Filters:
- Report filtering is not available when opening from the Reports tab.
- Filtering is available when tapping a dashboard widget to open the source report.

Report Features Not Available
Create, edit, or delete reports
Export
Print
Feed
Schedule report refreshes
Subscribe
Joined reports
Historical trend reports
Add to campaign
Role hierarchy
Custom summary formula fields
Folders
Hide details
Summary information

Other Notes about Using Reports
Drilling into reports with more than three checkbox fields is not available.
Error when viewing reports with more than 25 summary fields.

Considerations When Using Dashboards
View As: run dashboards as a user in your role hierarchy; choose from all users on the Salesforce mobile app.
Dashboard Layout: single-column layout on phones, up to two-column layout on tablets

Dashboards Features Not Available
Create, edit, or delete dashboards
Feed
Schedule
Link from a dashboard widget to a website or email address
Visualforce widgets on dashboards
Folders
Text widget
Image widget

Other Notes about Using Dashboards
Data in dashboard widgets can get out of sync with data in the report.
Refreshing a dashboard may not refresh its widgets.

Charts
Report charts are available after drilling into a dashboard widget's report; report charts aren't available from the Reports tab.
title: Reports and Dashboards Limitations in Salesforce Mobile App
